# shebok.ai — Cursor Rules

## Project
Bangladesh-first AI healthcare navigator. WhatsApp triage + conversational booking + doctor portal.
Stack: Next.js · Supabase · n8n · Groq · WhatsApp Cloud API · BanglaBERT · BioBERT · ChromaDB/pgvector.

## Architecture (v2.1 — no Twilio, no Meditron)
- **WhatsApp**: Meta WhatsApp Cloud API via n8n WhatsApp Business Cloud node (not Twilio).
- **Emergency detection**: (1) sync keyword hard gate, then (2) DeepSeek-R1 via Groq — same JSON schema Meditron used.
- **Triage + booking**: DeepSeek-R1 via Groq with separate system prompts.
- **Chitchat gate**: BanglaBERT local endpoint only.

## TypeScript / Next.js
- TypeScript strict mode always. No `any` — use `unknown` + Zod narrowing.
- Next.js 14+ App Router. Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when needed.
- Use `@/` import alias. Match existing shadcn/ui patterns in `apps/portal`.
- Validate all external JSON (LLM outputs, webhooks, DB writes) with Zod schemas before use.

## Database (Supabase)
- Never store raw phone numbers or NID — SHA-256 hash at ingestion only.
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` only in n8n workflows and Next.js server routes — never client bundles.
- All tables use RLS. Doctors query only their specialty + institution records.
- pgvector embeddings are 384-dim (S-PubMedBert-MS-MARCO).
- `clinical_observation` column stores DeepSeek emergency-pass framing (formerly meditron_observation).

## LLM Pipeline Rules
1. BanglaBERT: MEDICAL vs CHITCHAT only — not emergency detection.
2. Keyword hard gate runs synchronously BEFORE any LLM emergency call.
3. DeepSeek emergency pass: JSON `{ emergency_detected, primary_clinical_observation }` only.
4. DeepSeek triage: nurse persona, no diagnoses, no drug dosages. Strip `` blocks before patient text or DB insert.
5. BioBERT: runs ONLY after `triage_complete` — full conversation transcript.
6. Malformed LLM output → schema validation gate → auto-retry once → deterministic fallback.

## n8n Workflows
- WhatsApp trigger: WhatsApp Business Cloud node or Webhook + HTTP reply to Graph API.
- PII scrub (SHA-256) before any external API call.
- Emergency branch terminates pipeline — no triage, no booking nodes.
- Conversation state in Supabase JSON buffer, 24hr TTL.

## Security
- No secrets in code, commits, or client-side env.
- Patient text wrapped in delimiters before LLM calls.
- Open-weights / Groq-hosted models only — no OpenAI/Anthropic for live triage.

## File layout
- `apps/portal/` — Next.js doctor portal
- `services/ml/` — BanglaBERT + BioBERT Flask endpoints
- `services/pipeline/` — prompts, emergency keywords, Zod schemas
- `services/n8n/` — Docker compose + workflow exports
- `.env.local` at repo root — single source of truth for local dev
